social_posts.post_text: To say that I’m incredibly proud of all the 2021 Femi Gbede scholars will be an understatement. They were all admitted to the Nigerian bar this week as Barristers and Solicitors of the Supreme Court of Nigeria. Six of them made 1st Class and two made 2nd Class (Upper Division). Congratulations to all of you. Go, and prosper! @abas_esq @jewel_edotimeh @_chancetheattorney @_oluwabusola @sylver_odin @oluwadolapoowoyokun @omo_lade_mi

Buhari set to hand over to AG Baby
Ahead of his swearing in tomorrow as Nigeria's president for the month of February, Mr. Adam Gbede has called on his political rivals to sheathe their swords and join him in his efforts to rebuild the nation and revamp Nigeria's ailing economy. Speaking with newsmen at his Inanjo Ogiriosa residence yesterday, the two-year old  whiz kid, who defied all odds to clinch unexpected victory, asked Nigerians to brace up for the challenges ahead, even as he works his magic to deliver the dividends of democracy to all and sundry. Gbede won more than 25% of the votes in all 36 states of the federation including the FCT, in an election that pundits have described as historic and unprecedented. In fulfillment of his campaign promises, Gbede will on his first day in office, distribute cassava, agbado, ewa and garri to several communities. #fakenews
Happy to announce that the early cycle application for the 6th annual Femi Gbede Scholarship is now open.

Week 2 of the Africa Arbitration Academy, which I had the honor of co-founding some years ago, ended on a high note. This year’s program is special in many ways. We have 28 participants from 15 African countries in London, with an Ethiopian judge and the Attorney General of Malawi being part of the star-studded cohort. They all came with very rich experience and deep insights. At the end of the three week all-expense-paid program, participants return to their respective countries with a diploma.

social_posts.post_text: It is my pleasure to announce the 2023/2024 Femi Gbede law school scholars. The selection of all ten (10) of them reflects my judgment that they have the unbounded potentials to succeed given the necessary support and mentorship. Each of them is unique, with compelling stories of grit, determination and perseverance, even in the face of adversity. Please join me in congratulating @chimdi_awa @aropmeg @teejayesq @udentalota @telothebrand @becoming_lambish, Temitope Ogunsanwo, Adewale Adelaja, Morenike Oyeleke and Kelvin Ofodile. #lawschool #scholarship #nigeria
